</title>
<subSubSection id="B6B8B38973805C4997E4A76B7759D448" pageId="null" pageNumber="158" type="description">
<paragraph id="4CA7600BBE289BE8D28E5919C247DB08" pageId="null" pageNumber="158">
<emphasis id="989FEE7E70AEAA33BB6F91286A2E0D7E" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="158">
<normalizedToken id="37CE19C419BE8BE2536CB4AEBD95B5F7" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="158">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
breit lanzettlich bis oval, 2
</emphasis>
- 
<emphasis id="F8617101CEF712FAE8BB0D7C28E8BDFC" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="158">4mal so lang wie breit</emphasis>
, 
<normalizedToken id="BDD1EA9BB59A62464B1B3089A68E26A3" originalValue="plötzlich" pageId="null" pageNumber="158">ploetzlich</normalizedToken>
in den kurzen Stiel 
<normalizedToken id="98F3FB5481799EF2985D6686E50ABAA2" originalValue="verschmälert" pageId="null" pageNumber="158">verschmaelert</normalizedToken>
, 
<emphasis id="78BC6523721B51AC2AC4A24EF0DDE0D4" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="158">
<normalizedToken id="CBD703A39B66F50B1A17874488E8F5DC" originalValue="grün" pageId="null" pageNumber="158">gruen</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
, kahl. 
<normalizedToken id="868AF64AF42773234F5A7FD78576DC19" originalValue="Blüten" pageId="null" pageNumber="158">Blueten</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="4380AABBBA54E0826286EAAEE3498127" originalValue="Blütenstiele" pageId="null" pageNumber="158">Bluetenstiele</normalizedToken>
und Frucht 
<normalizedToken id="A16D73E039E8970158C8F343153CF089" originalValue="ähnlich" pageId="null" pageNumber="158">aehnlich</normalizedToken>
wie bei 
<taxonomicName id="92B78CA7E8A2EF1CE107C0F038592B50" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Lycium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="null" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="halimifolium">
<emphasis id="0F849F85161D3AC6DBCC45A2A77F64C6" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="158">
<authorityName id="7DE62E2B24F550E6D2C71BCC34EE747D" pageId="null" pageNumber="158">L.</authorityName>
halimifolium
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 1), aber die 
<emphasis id="2F027EFA5EFEECF783839144014F4648" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="158">
<normalizedToken id="8360082EFBC06273C812331C8125D0F8" originalValue="Blüten" pageId="null" pageNumber="158">Blueten</normalizedToken>
purpurviolett; Kronzipfel so lang oder etwas 
<normalizedToken id="A3D3AAD5DDB2A803F7B4ECB4C29FA4E8" originalValue="länger" pageId="null" pageNumber="158">laenger</normalizedToken>
als die 
<normalizedToken id="3F9A71F8DFEE8AA350D1127E6F4F73B7" originalValue="Kronröhre" pageId="null" pageNumber="158">Kronroehre</normalizedToken>
;
</emphasis>
Frucht rot. - 
<normalizedToken id="6BADF49A4B5CED2A1CC37F4F563C0AAF" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="158">Bluete</normalizedToken>
: 
<normalizedToken id="9258EB672F8E54EC053D411B843819B9" originalValue="Frühling" pageId="null" pageNumber="158">Fruehling</normalizedToken>
bis Herbst.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D96053DE8BCA86882603083119DC8EF" pageId="null" pageNumber="158">
<emphasis id="A9CF87F411A8F12B5FC13499D5B78F15" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="158">Zytologische Angaben. 2n</emphasis>
= 
<emphasis id="D9E3D4FA7D5F266815E7E2B12183F397" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="158">24:</emphasis>
Material aus botanischem Garten und Japan (Morinaga et al. 1929, Sugiura aus Darlington und Wylie 1955).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="58B87BAF9A0F81EE1D18A0317C9DE6D6" pageId="null" pageNumber="158">
<emphasis id="AFA21DA3CB6BA5726D726AB2206D23D3" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="158">Standort.</emphasis>
Kollin. Lockere, steinige oder sandige 
<normalizedToken id="5C5E0B10E05DE254179CF0E496F69E9A" originalValue="Böden" pageId="null" pageNumber="158">Boeden</normalizedToken>
in warmen Lagen. Hecken.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7C832842C4F94A6740A5B50373E05AEA" pageId="null" pageNumber="158">
<emphasis id="77965EB5F6F2CC5BD2C787D9979526F8" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="158">Verbreitung. Ostasiatische Pflanze</emphasis>
(China, Mandschurei, Japan); in Europa als Zierstrauch 
<normalizedToken id="0C2B972B100482BCE429C992CD879E63" originalValue="eingeführt" pageId="null" pageNumber="158">eingefuehrt</normalizedToken>
. - Im Gebiet: Gelegentlich als Zierstrauch angepflanzt und selten verwildert (z. B. 
<normalizedToken id="87B5FBFFEF1288C72BE683DFE003899F" originalValue="Elsaß" pageId="null" pageNumber="158">Elsass</normalizedToken>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
